            "title": "Salesforce to Acquire Software Firm Apromore",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Dean Seal </p><br/><p>\n  Salesforce said it has agreed to acquire Apromore, a provider of process intelligence software, in a deal with undisclosed financial terms. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The customer-relationship management platform said Thursday that adding Apromore's suite of process intelligence capabilities will accelerate its vision for agentic process automation, or the use of AI agents to complete high-level business tasks. </p><p>\n\n  \"Apromore gives customers the end-to-end visibility they need to understand how their business truly operates,\" Salesforce Chief Product Officer Steve Fisher said. </p><p>\n\n  The transaction is expected to close in the fourth quarter of fiscal 2026. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Dean Seal at dean.seal@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  10-09-25 1717ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/salesforce-to-acquire-software-firm-apromore-ce7d5adada8ff625",
